This paper is primarily focused on natural language learning through multi-agent communication, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for this purpose, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also explores changes to the game environment to improve the semantic properties of the induced "word meanings," which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the development of machines that can communicate with humans, which could fall under the category of neural engineering (cs.NE).
